{
  "title": "AD #11 · Government Regulation (Path A · Evaluate)",
  "lessons": [
    {
      "translation": "我同意政府监管能让社会受益，但只能到某种程度。",
      "phrases": ["I agree that", "government regulation", "can benefit society,", "but only up to a point."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "一旦过度使用，它会压抑创造力，拖慢创新。",
      "phrases": ["When overused,", "it can stifle creativity", "and slow innovation."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "Claire 提出了一个合理的点：政府监管能阻止企业伤害公众。",
      "phrases": ["Claire raises a valid point", "in that", "government regulation", "can prevent companies", "from harming the public."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "但 Andrew 最终更有说服力，因为过度监管会推高成本、降低效率。",
      "phrases": ["However,", "Andrew is ultimately more convincing", "because excessive regulation", "can increase costs", "and reduce efficiency."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "主要原因是企业和政府的优先事项不同。",
      "phrases": ["The main reason is that", "companies and governments", "have different priorities."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "企业被利润和竞争驱动。",
      "phrases": ["Companies are driven by", "profit and competition."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "这给了它们强烈的动力去降成本、简化流程、采用新技术。",
      "phrases": ["This gives them", "a strong incentive", "to reduce costs,", "streamline procedures,", "and adopt new technologies."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "因此，企业更可能聚焦创新和效率，而不是公共福祉。",
      "phrases": ["As a result,", "companies are more likely", "to focus on", "innovation and productivity", "than on public welfare."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "相反，政府应当关注公共福祉，而不是为每个行业设计细致方案。",
      "phrases": ["By contrast,", "governments should focus on", "public welfare", "rather than designing", "detailed plans", "for each industry."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "比如，政府应当要求餐厅满足食品安全标准，但不应规定厨师如何设计菜单。",
      "phrases": ["For example,", "governments should require restaurants", "to meet food safety standards,", "but they should not dictate", "how chefs design their menus."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "总的来说，最好的路径是有限度的监管——保护公众，同时给企业足够的创新空间。",
      "phrases": ["Overall,", "the best approach is", "limited regulation", "that protects the public", "while still allowing businesses", "enough freedom to innovate."]
    }
  ]
}
